        "monster_family": {
          "name": "Orchid Mantis",
          "subtype": "monster_family",
          "type": "stat_block_section"
        },
        "name": "Orchid Mantis",
        "sections": [
          {
            "name": "Animal Masters",
            "sources": [
              {
                "link": {
                  "alt": "Tian Xia World Guide pg. 292",
                  "aonid": 223,
                  "game-obj": "Sources",
                  "name": "Tian Xia World Guide pg. 292",
                  "type": "link"
                },
                "name": "Tian Xia World Guide",
                "page": 292,
                "type": "source"
              }
            ],
            "text": "While many sapient beings like to put themselves above the animal kingdom, the gap can be closer than many realize and catch the arrogant off guard. Tian stories abound with tales of masters learning mystic or martial arts from animals, though many scholars dismiss these creatures as powerful beings simply taking animal form. The five-color mantis is a strong counterargument to the latter claims, as are animals who undergo the transformation into yaoguai. Rarer tales speak of mimic birds who cast spells that they overhear or larvae that cocoon themselves into artifact shells and pupate into living weapons.",
            "type": "section"
          },
          {
            "links": [
              {
                "alt": "plant form",
                "aonid": 121,
                "game-obj": "Familiars",
                "name": "plant form",
                "type": "link"
              }
            ],
            "name": "Colorful Companions",
            "sources": [
              {
                "link": {
                  "alt": "Tian Xia World Guide pg. 292",
                  "aonid": 223,
                  "game-obj": "Sources",
                  "name": "Tian Xia World Guide pg. 292",
                  "type": "link"
                },
                "name": "Tian Xia World Guide",
                "page": 292,
                "type": "source"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Orchid mantises are common choices for familiars, even beyond their natural range. At the GM's discretion, such familiars can take the plant form familiar ability, despite not being plants themselves, to represent and enhance their exceptional camouflage.",
            "type": "section"
          },
          {
            "name": "Elemental Blossoms",
            "sources": [
              {
                "link": {
                  "alt": "Tian Xia World Guide pg. 292",
                  "aonid": 223,
                  "game-obj": "Sources",
                  "name": "Tian Xia World Guide pg. 292",
                  "type": "link"
                },
                "name": "Tian Xia World Guide",
                "page": 292,
                "type": "source"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Undisturbed forests, forgotten valleys, and medicinal gardens hide plants that carry elemental or magical essences. Hiding among these flowers, mantises grow stronger with the rich environment, preying on the other fabulous creatures living among the blossoms, such as apothecary bees",
            "type": "section"
          }
        ],
        "sources": [
          {
            "link": {
              "alt": "Tian Xia World Guide pg. 292",
              "aonid": 223,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Tian Xia World Guide pg. 292",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Tian Xia World Guide",
            "page": 292,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "Few creatures appear as beautiful as the orchid mantises. Their elegant form and coloration resemble flowers, and many people adopt the delicate creatures as short-lived pets. While these mundane insects aren't dangerous to humanoids, they can still bring down prey several times their own size. Unfolding from their flowery pose, orchid mantises lash out with blinding speed, even chasing foraging butterflies with their sharp-toothed arms and powerful bite.",
        "type": "monster_family"
      },
